28/02/2010
VANCOUVER, Canada -- Croatia's Ivica Kostelic won his second silver medal of the Winter Olympics on Saturday (February 27th), this time in the Men's Slalom. Italy's Giuliano Razzoli edged past him to win gold by just .17 of a second. Kostelic, 30, won silver in the Super-Combined on February 21st. (BBC-10/02/27)
